Company: Forte Interactive, Children's Service Council of Palm Beach County, Ocean Reef Community Association
Description of incident: Information Forte Interactive inadvertently copied from web applications used by Children's Service Council and Ocean Reef Community accidentally became publicly accessible after a system upgrade.  Names, Social Security numbers, driver's license numbers, and dates of birth of individuals whose information was contained in the web portal or web portals was publicly accessible between December 7, 2011 and February 3, 2012. The issue was discovered on January 30, 2012.
